Amanda Khoza(File) (Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash;&nbsp;Two people were killed in the early hours of Thursday in an accident involving two buses, a truck and two cows near Harding, KZN EMS said. Emergency Medical Services spokesperson Robert McKenzie said paramedics arrived on scene and&nbsp;found&nbsp;one bus lying on its side and over 50 people having&nbsp;sustained injuries. &ldquo;Paramedics worked rapidly to assess and triage all the patients. Due to the number of casualties, additional vehicles were dispatched from Port Shepstone to assist at the scene.&rdquo; He said paramedics treated 52 patients. &ldquo;Nine patients were in a serious condition, while 43 of the patients had sustained minor injuries,&rdquo; said McKenzie. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.